WEBVTT

00:32.898 --> 01:00.882
again welcome back to our our study of Proverbs and we are in Proverbs chapter 7 and we're going to look today at verses 19 and 20 so let's read them Proverbs chapter 7 let me find it here in my Bible 19 and 20 let me give you a little bit of introduction so this

01:01.218 --> 01:06.105
this woman who we are saying represents the way the world would treat us.

01:06.866 --> 01:16.620
She's been wandering around in the streets and she has been looking for a young man to tempt and deceive and to lead him into sin.

01:16.680 --> 01:25.673
Now, we're going to look in verse 19 and 20, one of her arguments that she's going to use in order to try to get him to sin.

01:25.734 --> 01:28.818
So she says in verse 19,

01:29.570 --> 01:31.632
For my husband is not at home.

01:31.672 --> 01:33.975
He is gone on a long journey.

01:34.535 --> 01:37.419
He has taken a bag of money with him.

01:37.479 --> 01:41.043
At the full moon, he will come home.

01:42.024 --> 01:43.545
All right, let's go to the Lord in prayer.

01:48.110 --> 01:58.802
Father, I come before you and I pray for every person, parents and children that may be watching this

01:59.490 --> 02:00.271
this segment.

02:03.856 --> 02:14.189
Father, we are so small and our words have no power, but your word and your spirit, Lord, can do all things.

02:15.691 --> 02:27.346
I pray that you would use this, this teaching, this time of sharing that all would see that you are the God who sees

02:28.258 --> 02:32.344
And that can be both good news and bad news.

02:34.307 --> 02:41.298
For the faithful believer, Lord, in time of trouble, it is good news to know that you are the God who sees.

02:43.021 --> 02:51.694
But for the wayward one, the one who's rebellious, who thinks that they sin and get away with it, that they're hidden.

02:52.555 --> 02:54.979
Lord, this is not just bad news.

02:55.099 --> 02:57.042
It's it's terrifying news.

02:57.986 --> 03:12.100
And I pray that you would make that a reality in the lives of, in my life, but also in the lives, Lord, of those who listen in Jesus' name, amen.

03:13.261 --> 03:26.514
So this lady is trying to draw this, she's a married woman, she's trying to draw this young man to her house, and she's trying to convince him to enter into sin,

03:27.330 --> 03:31.254
And one of the things that she tells him is that, hey, my husband's gone.

03:32.435 --> 03:35.498
We're not going to get caught.

03:36.319 --> 03:42.285
And that's one of the things that the world and the devil will constantly set before the believer.

03:42.605 --> 03:47.230
Hey, you can do this and no one will see it.

03:47.690 --> 03:49.672
Now, here's what you need to understand.

03:50.613 --> 03:55.538
It is very possible that no human being

03:55.618 --> 03:57.240
We'll see you do that.

03:58.502 --> 04:06.715
It is possible, not likely, but it is possible that you will get away with whatever, whatever sin you're committing.

04:07.115 --> 04:11.923
That is possible with regard to men, but it is highly unlikely.

04:12.283 --> 04:14.126
And then something else you need to understand.

04:14.627 --> 04:24.562
Every time you go back and commit that sin, the chances are increasing exponentially that you will get caught

04:24.994 --> 04:28.237
by men sooner or later.

04:29.358 --> 04:45.794
You know, detective work and forensic work, it has so advanced that sometimes I'll watch these programs or read a book where they catch criminals in the most extraordinary way.

04:46.795 --> 04:53.842
I mean, finding just a piece of grass on the front of a car that is found in the same place where

04:53.986 --> 04:56.028
a murder or a crime occurred.

04:56.348 --> 05:03.955
It's unbelievable what men can do, what investigators can do to track and find a criminal.

05:05.096 --> 05:23.954
And it's even going to become more and more difficult as they start to develop and use AI for better, for worse, at the same time it is going to increase the potential of discovering who is committing crimes.

05:24.866 --> 05:26.588
Now, here's what I want you to see.

05:26.628 --> 05:33.397
It's almost impossible if you continue and sin that you will not get caught by men.

05:36.521 --> 05:49.298
But it is impossible to think that you can avoid God, that you can do something, that you can commit a sin that God will not see.

05:49.474 --> 05:51.356
So I want you to look at a few things here.

05:51.396 --> 06:05.370
I want us to look at just in the book of Proverbs, in the book of Ecclesiastes, in Proverbs 5, 21, it said, for the ways of a man are before the eyes of the Lord, and he watches all his paths.

06:06.110 --> 06:07.972
It says the ways of a man.

06:08.132 --> 06:11.956
It's implural here, indicating every way.

06:11.996 --> 06:18.002
That's not just every deed, not just every word,

06:18.242 --> 06:27.791
but even every thought of a man is not sometimes before the Lord, but it is constantly before the Lord.

06:28.212 --> 06:33.697
It's not that the Lord looks over here, and while he's looking over here, he doesn't see you over there.

06:34.197 --> 06:47.250
The Lord is everywhere in all his fullness, and he knows everything that is going on, and he knows it immediately, perfectly,

06:47.746 --> 06:49.688
without the need of investigation.

06:49.809 --> 06:51.851
He simply knows it.

06:52.352 --> 06:56.717
And it says, he watches over all our paths.

06:58.099 --> 07:00.122
There's no place that we can go.

07:00.142 --> 07:12.938
I remember hearing a story where a young man, he was kind of reverse the roles, a young man was trying to get a young girl to do things with him that were sinful.

07:14.100 --> 07:16.082
And she said, okay, I'll do it.

07:17.154 --> 07:21.919
If you can take me somewhere where no one can see us.

07:23.061 --> 07:27.365
And he took her to various places and she kept saying, no, we can be found out here.

07:27.425 --> 07:28.967
We can be found out here.

07:29.368 --> 07:30.569
We can be seen here.

07:30.589 --> 07:35.314
And in the end, he said, how could anybody see us in all these places?

07:35.855 --> 07:40.139
And she said, God can see us in all these places.

07:41.161 --> 07:41.781
And that's true.

07:42.502 --> 07:43.683
Now, I want you to think about this.

07:43.783 --> 07:46.066
We talk about the omniscience of God.

07:46.658 --> 07:48.921
the all knowledge of God.

07:50.463 --> 08:01.837
So we're not just saying that he looks and he can figure it out over a period of time or he can put several things together and eventually he's going to figure out what's going on.

08:02.638 --> 08:04.119
Remember the language I used?

08:04.480 --> 08:07.043
He knows everything perfectly.

08:08.545 --> 08:11.769
He knows everything immediately.

08:11.829 --> 08:12.810
There's no delay.

08:12.870 --> 08:15.954
He knows everything

08:16.066 --> 08:23.175
without the need for an investigation, without the need for making a calculation.

08:23.235 --> 08:26.720
I had a friend in college and he was so smart.

08:27.601 --> 08:41.138
And you could just throw these incredible formulas at him, mathematical problems at him, and just it seemed like he would answer 10 times faster than everyone else in the classroom.

08:41.158 --> 08:44.402
I'm back there trying to figure it out in my head and he's just boom.

08:44.738 --> 08:46.280
every time, boom, boom.

08:46.801 --> 08:55.051
He was fast, but he had to calculate, he had to think, he had to take putting one number to another number to another number.

08:55.591 --> 08:56.613
God isn't like that.

08:57.614 --> 09:00.818
He knows everything exhaustively.

09:00.878 --> 09:03.301
That means there's nothing outside of his knowledge.

09:03.561 --> 09:05.364
He knows it immediately.

09:05.424 --> 09:13.714
And without calculation, without investigation, he doesn't send an angel from his throne.

09:14.018 --> 09:18.103
and say, go figure this out for me or go find that kind of news.

09:18.404 --> 09:19.285
He knows it all.

09:19.745 --> 09:20.726
You say, how can that be?

09:20.767 --> 09:23.951
Well, what you have to realize is God is not like us.

09:24.291 --> 09:25.472
We are physical.

09:25.673 --> 09:26.734
We are matter.

09:27.175 --> 09:27.936
We are flesh.

09:28.657 --> 09:29.638
God is spirit.

09:30.639 --> 09:35.525
So functions in a completely different realm.

09:35.585 --> 09:42.514
That's why I'm always telling young people, you know, don't say keep God number one because you're assuming

09:42.594 --> 09:48.521
that God is on a list with the rest of us and he's like us just bigger and better.

09:48.741 --> 09:49.462
That's not true.

09:50.122 --> 09:54.607
What you have to understand is God is not on a list.

09:55.669 --> 10:01.155
He's in a category all to himself and everyone else is in another category.

10:01.215 --> 10:09.324
Now you can put everyone else on a list, but you can't put God on that list because he's in a completely different box.

10:10.025 --> 10:10.245
Okay.

10:10.986 --> 10:11.346
Now,

10:11.490 --> 10:12.671
Proverbs 15-3.

10:13.152 --> 10:18.178
It says, the eyes of the Lord are in every place.

10:19.579 --> 10:20.320
Now think about that.

10:21.542 --> 10:22.382
Every place.

10:24.205 --> 10:32.294
Not just in an open field, but in the deepest, deepest recess or cave that exists on the planet.

10:32.814 --> 10:35.598
He's at the surface of the ocean.

10:36.058 --> 10:39.442
He is at the very bottom of the ocean.

10:40.674 --> 10:46.901
He knows the farthest star, his eyes are on the farthest star.

10:47.301 --> 10:51.706
His eyes are on everything at one time.

10:52.447 --> 10:53.048
Do you see that?

10:53.448 --> 10:55.711
The eyes of the Lord are in every place.

10:56.551 --> 11:00.836
Now listen to this, watching the evil and the good.

11:01.297 --> 11:02.658
And so what do we have here?

11:02.698 --> 11:04.460
We have bad news, don't wait.

11:05.081 --> 11:09.746
And we have good news that if you're doing good,

11:10.658 --> 11:18.288
If you're being faithful, even though no one else is seeing you, no one else is watching you, you know that he is.

11:19.710 --> 11:35.251
But also, if you're doing evil, if you're getting away with crime after crime after crime and no one sees you and no one ever catches you, he sees you and he will catch you.

11:35.872 --> 11:40.658
You know, I was preaching in a prison several months ago,

11:40.866 --> 11:53.424
And I kept hearing this complaint from the prisoners that they were in prison because they were, they admitted, they committed crimes, but that they were in prison because, well, they were poor.

11:53.904 --> 11:57.890
They had no power and they couldn't defend themselves.

11:59.152 --> 12:06.322
Then they would say, but there are wealthy, wealthy, powerful, powerful men, businessmen, politicians,

12:06.786 --> 12:14.295
that commit crimes that are even worse than the crimes they committed, that the prisoners committed, and yet they never go to prison.

12:14.776 --> 12:15.577
You know what I told them?

12:16.558 --> 12:20.303
I said, the fact that you're in prison is a gift from God.

12:21.184 --> 12:26.450
He is stopping you now in your crimes, showing you you're wrong.

12:26.811 --> 12:34.440
He's catching you, allowing you to be caught and giving you an opportunity to see your sin, repent and be saved.

12:35.061 --> 12:36.082
With those other men,

12:36.610 --> 12:41.075
He's allowing them to get away with it and get away with it and get away with it.

12:41.635 --> 12:43.437
That's not so much mercy.

12:44.058 --> 12:44.839
That's judgment.

12:46.160 --> 12:50.565
Because when they die, then there's no hope of redemption.

12:51.746 --> 13:02.738
So when you see people and you're going to, when you get older, young people, you're going to see rich and powerful people who get away with everything and they laugh about it.

13:04.034 --> 13:11.204
They'll condemn others who commit lesser crimes, but they themselves will get away with it until they die.

13:12.606 --> 13:15.089
Then they will stand before God.

13:16.030 --> 13:25.243
Another thing I want to point out to you because, you know, your kids and I need to take every opportunity to apply what we're learning.

13:26.945 --> 13:33.714
It is a grace from God when your parents catch you doing something wrong.

13:35.554 --> 13:42.844
When your parents find out that you did something, you told a lie, you were mean to your sister, whatever, that is a grace.

13:44.466 --> 13:48.431
And if that your parents respond properly, they will rebuke you.

13:48.472 --> 13:49.453
They will correct you.

13:49.493 --> 13:50.895
They will even discipline you.

13:51.195 --> 13:54.960
And even though that discipline may hurt, it is a grace.

13:55.281 --> 14:03.672
God is exposing your sin so that you don't just keep going on and on and on and getting worse and worse and worse.

14:04.734 --> 14:05.074
Now,

14:05.730 --> 14:19.050
Let's look at one last verse here, Ecclesiastes 12, 14, for God will bring every act to judgment, everything which is hidden, whether it is good or evil.

14:19.792 --> 14:22.235
Again, I've got good news.

14:23.337 --> 14:25.901
God sees every faithful act.

14:26.742 --> 14:28.144
I've got bad news.

14:28.785 --> 14:32.892
God sees every faithless act.

14:33.493 --> 14:34.354
And not only

14:34.434 --> 14:42.603
As it says in the other text, not only does he see it, but it says God will bring it to judgment.

14:46.347 --> 14:53.936
There is coming a day when both you and I will stand before God.

14:55.217 --> 15:02.866
Now, if he judges us for every sin, every crime that we have ever committed,

15:03.298 --> 15:05.301
there is absolutely no hope.

15:06.362 --> 15:22.042
The only hope we have is trusting in Christ, because when he was on the cross, all our crimes, everything that we did, both in public and in secret, that was sin, it was placed on him.

15:22.082 --> 15:25.366
And he suffered and paid the price for it.

15:25.627 --> 15:31.474
And if we trust in Christ now, then when we stand before him in judgment,

15:32.834 --> 15:34.876
We will be justified.

15:35.217 --> 15:38.300
We will be declared right before God.

15:38.840 --> 15:42.785
We will be invited into the fullness of His kingdom.

15:43.966 --> 15:48.451
You know, it's very interesting in the book of Revelation when it talks about the great white throne judgment.

15:49.031 --> 15:51.654
It talks about the books being opened.

15:52.535 --> 15:53.877
Notice it doesn't say book.

15:54.117 --> 15:58.401
There's a book of life and then there's books of all our deeds.

15:58.842 --> 16:02.706
The idea that's being presented there is God knows

16:02.818 --> 16:16.239
every one of your thoughts, every one of your deeds, he knows you better than you know yourself, and he doesn't forget anything that you do or I do.

16:17.341 --> 16:26.175
And if we're judged by those books without Christ, there is no hope.

16:26.195 --> 16:30.802
Now, before we go, I want to say one other thing.

16:33.058 --> 16:33.960
How can I say this?

16:34.300 --> 16:45.920
You know Jesus, especially in the Book of Matthew and the Sermon on the Mount, he warns about doing our righteousness before men to be seen by them.

16:47.122 --> 16:56.338
It seems like today, you know with all these, what do you call them, selfies, that no one can experience or do anything

16:56.546 --> 17:04.897
and feel complete about it unless they take a picture of themselves or they film themselves doing something and then post it for everyone to see.

17:05.898 --> 17:06.519
It's amazing.

17:06.539 --> 17:18.495
It's like you have an experience, you're out hiking in a beautiful place and there's a beautiful sunset and, but you're not happy unless you get a picture of it and you can post it for everyone to see.

17:18.535 --> 17:26.546
I've seen, you know, preachers who will go out, you know, and they preach in the streets, but they, they film themselves.

17:26.658 --> 17:32.626
And then feel like they've got to, it's no good unless they present it all before the public to see.

17:33.287 --> 17:34.769
Let me share with you one thing.

17:34.829 --> 17:37.813
It's a truth that has meant the world to me.

17:39.175 --> 17:43.802
And it's simply this, God is the God who sees.

17:46.545 --> 17:51.572
I don't have to be seen by the public because God sees me.

17:52.473 --> 17:53.795
You don't have to be seen.

17:54.056 --> 17:55.858
You don't have to be rewarded.

17:56.258 --> 17:57.579
by the public.

17:57.599 --> 18:00.682
You don't have to be applauded by the public.

18:00.982 --> 18:08.710
You don't have to do things in the side of men for some sort of recognition because God is watching you always.

18:09.270 --> 18:11.893
He is the God who sees.

18:13.254 --> 18:16.757
When you come to understand that, then you start realizing something.

18:17.598 --> 18:23.484
Actually, if you're going to seek to do something, don't seek to do it publicly.

18:23.524 --> 18:25.746
Seek to do its

18:26.082 --> 18:32.370
privately hidden so that only God sees what you're doing.

18:33.031 --> 18:33.732
It's amazing.

18:33.912 --> 18:48.611
The young person, listen to me, you're going to go through times when no one understands you, when no one understands how much you're suffering, how much you're hurting, when no one's going to understand the unfulfilled desires and everything that you have.

18:50.874 --> 18:54.098
Isn't it a comfort to know that God sees

18:56.002 --> 19:02.150
And he knows and he understands completely and that you don't have to be famous.

19:03.732 --> 19:09.799
You don't have to do your works before men and be recognized because God is watching.

19:10.260 --> 19:16.748
And if you do the good, his will, you will be rewarded in heaven.

19:17.408 --> 19:21.013
Let me give you a philosophical question and we'll end with that.

19:23.376 --> 19:25.298
Why would God plant?

19:25.698 --> 19:40.379
the most beautiful flower he's ever created in a forest so deep that no man, no angel will ever walk through it.

19:41.280 --> 19:45.486
How is God glorified by a flower that's so hidden?

19:46.728 --> 19:53.938
He's glorified by that flower because he sees it every day and delights in it.

19:55.010 --> 20:04.825
One of the things that I tell, especially preachers, is this, that their life should be like the tip of an iceberg.

20:05.867 --> 20:06.568
And what do I mean?

20:07.549 --> 20:14.620
When you see a tip of an iceberg coming out of the water, you do know right that that's the smallest part of the iceberg.

20:15.321 --> 20:17.965
That's just the part that's exposed.

20:18.586 --> 20:21.130
And underneath it is huge.

20:21.971 --> 20:23.794
That's the way our lives ought to be.

20:24.386 --> 20:30.014
that our public life is only this small part of who we are.

20:30.996 --> 20:50.365
The big part of us is our private life, our personal relationship with Christ through the Word of God, through prayer, and through walking with Him in obedience when no one else is looking.

20:51.206 --> 20:51.567
Okay?

20:52.869 --> 20:53.810
Yeah.

20:53.986 --> 21:00.875
will be hidden and will be looking to him knowing that he's always looking back.

21:02.217 --> 21:02.557
All right.

21:03.959 --> 21:08.064
So if you clean your room and mom and dad don't notice it.

21:09.045 --> 21:09.586
Don't worry.

21:10.687 --> 21:11.208
God does.

21:12.370 --> 21:12.890
Let's pray.

21:17.836 --> 21:19.439
Father, thank you for your word.

21:20.420 --> 21:22.162
And I pray that you would use it.

21:24.130 --> 21:26.113
Oh dear God, use your word.

21:26.133 --> 21:45.340
Use the wisdom of Scripture in the life of the young boys and girls, teenagers, parents that may listen to these little simple devotions.

21:45.360 --> 21:49.906
Use your word word in their life.

